The following table shows a summary
of the top 50 most expensive office markets taken from 
CBRE Global Research and Consulting’s Prime Office Occupancy 
Costs survey.  The survey, conducted twice yearly, compares office 
occupation costs for prime  office space  in 133 cities worldwide
as of March 31, 2012.  Note 1: (*) Annual cost.
Note 2: Occupancy cost represents rent, plus local taxes, and 
service charges.  Source: CBRE Global Research and Consulting  To contact the reporter on this story:
